FBIS3-16250 "drsov050_a_94019" FBIS-SOV-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS British Agent High-Ranking Member of Arms Industry LD1403160094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1406 GMT 14 Mar 94 LD1403160094 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] A well-informed source in Russia's Federal Counterintelligence Service confirmed that the British agent detained in Moscow last January was Russian citizen Vadim Sintsov, who held a high post in the arms industry concern SMM. According to the Federal Counterintelligence Service, he passed over information about Russia's defense potential and test defense projects to British intelligence agencies. The source did not confirm, however, that Sintsov had worked with the British intelligence agencies since 1986. He said that he had been recruited much later, but refused to give the exact time or assess the damage inflicted on Russia.
